From Steve Chesney x Subject Re Diamond SS X In article A , writes Greetings I've had a bunch of problems with the x Opening a DOS window on the desktop can occasionally result in the windows blowing up into a set of horizontal lines, hashing the entire desktop Nothing can recover this except to completely exit from Windows The other irritating problem is that windows that scroll often overwrite lines rather than actually I posted a similar query and got these replies which I am testing so far so good turn hardware scrolling off before going into windows xmode scrolloff in the pif file for dos window, set emulate text mode get the latest drivers from the DiamoND BBS or cica dates are Steve Chesney Metaphase Technology Inc voice North Lexington Avenue fax Arden Hills, MN